****[[Gothic language|Gothic]]: {{lang|got|fairguni}} ({{lang|got|𐍆𐌰𐌹𐍂𐌲𐌿𐌽𐌹}}), '(wooded) mountain', and {{lang|got|fairhus}}, 'world', [[Old English]]: {{lang|ang|firgen}}, 'mountain', 'wooded hill',{{Sfn|Kroonen|2013|p=136}}{{sfn|Lajoye|Oudaer|2014|p=52}}
