**[[Nuristani languages|Nuristani]]: Pärun (or ''Pērūneî''), a war god worshipped in [[Kafiristan]] (present-day [[Nuristan Province]], [[Afghanistan]]),{{Sfn|Mallory|Adams|1997|p=582–583}}{{Sfn|Jackson|2002|p=75–76}}
**[[Persian language|Persian]]: [[Piran Viseh|Piran (Viseh)]], a heroic figure present in the [[Shahnameh]], the [[national epic]] of [[Greater Iran]]; it has been suggested his name might be related to the [[Slavic religion|Slavic]] deity [[Perun]],<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Lajoye |first=Patrice |date=2012 |title=There is no "Perun in the Caucasus"... But Maybe an Ancient Iranian Thunder Demon |journal=[[Studia Mythologica Slavica]] |language=en |volume=15 |pages=179–184 |doi=10.3986/sms.v15i1.1582 |issn=1581-128X |doi-access=free}}</ref>
