**[[Celtiberian language|Celtiberian]]: ''berkunetakam'' ('Perkunetaka'), a word attested in the [[Botorrita plaque|Botorrita Plate I]] and interpreted as a sacred oak grove,{{Sfn|De Bernardo|2009|p=|pp=11–12}}<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Adrados |first=Francisco R. |date=1995 |title=Propuestas para la interpretación de Botorrita 1 |journal=Emerita |language=es |volume=63 |issue=1 |pages=1–16 |doi=10.3989/emerita.1995.v63.i1.348 |issn=1988-8384 |doi-access=free}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |last=Adrados |first=Francisco R. |date=2002 |title=Sobre Botorrita IV |journal=Emerita |language=es |volume=70 |issue=1 |pages=1–8 |doi=10.3989/emerita.2002.v70.i1.118 |issn=1988-8384 |doi-access=free}}</ref>
