**[[Irish mythology|Irish]]: [[Erc mac Cairpri|Erc (mac Cairpri)]], mentioned at the end of ''[[Táin Bó Cúailnge]]'', and placed on the [[Kingship of Tara|throne of Tara]] by [[Conchobar mac Nessa]] in ''Cath Ruis na Ríg for Bóinn'';{{sfn|Lajoye|Oudaer|2014|p=|pp=40–41}} although an alternative etymology from [[Proto-Indo-European language|PIE]] {{lang|ine-x-proto|perk-}} ('color') > {{lang|ine-x-proto|perk-no}} ('[spotted] fish') has been proposed by [[Eric P. Hamp|Hamp]] and [[Ranko Matasović|Matasović]].{{sfn|Lajoye|Oudaer|2014|p=|pp=50–51}}
